contentrichtext.text: '''[[George Buchanan]]''' (1506–1582) was a Scottish humanist. '''George Buchanan''' may also refer to: *Sir [[George Buchanan (soldier)]] (died 1651), Scottish soldier during the Wars of the Three Kingdoms *Sir [[George Buchanan (physician)]] (1831–1895), [[Chief Medical Officer (United Kingdom)|Chief Medical Officer]] *Sir [[George Buchanan (diplomat)]] (1854–1924), British diplomat *[[George Buchanan (engineer born 1790)]] (1790–1852), Scottish civil engineer and land surveyor *[[George Buchanan (engineer born 1834)]] *Sir [[George Buchanan (engineer born 1865)]] (1865–1940), British civil engineer *[[George Buchanan (politician)]] (1890–1955), Scottish politician *[[George Wesley Buchanan]], professor of theology *[[George A. Buchanan]], winner of the Medal of Honor for actions in the American Civil War *[[George Buchanan (bishop)]], former Anglican Bishop of Johannesburg {{hndis|Buchanan, George}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Buchanan, George}}
